{"analytics_identifier":null,"base_path":"/government/organisations/flood-forecasting-centre/about/recruitment","content_id":"2ac17710-6c01-4d45-a4bd-346ca52dff7c","description":"How to apply for jobs at the Flood Forecasting Centre.","details":{"attachments":[],"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><h2 id=\"current-vacancies\">Current vacancies</h2>\n\n<p>There are no current vacancies.</p>\n\n<p>You can sign up to receive job alerts from:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://environmentagencyjobs.tal.net/vx/appcentre-1/candidate/\">Environment Agency</a></li>\n  <li><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.metoffice.gov.uk/about-us/careers/vacancies\">Met Office</a></li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2 id=\"our-team-and-how-we-work\">Our team and how we work</h2>\n\n<p><a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://youtu.be/7MJADza_1GE\">Working in the FFC</a></p>\n\n<h3 id=\"meaningful-work\">Meaningful work</h3>\n\n<p>The Flood Forecasting Centre (FFC):</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>plays a critical role in protecting lives, communities, and infrastructure</li>\n  <li>provides <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/flood-forecasting-centre/about/about-our-services\">essential flood forecasts and guidance</a> to responders and decision makers in England and Wales</li>\n  <li>supports decisions that directly affect how flood events are prepared for and dealt with</li>\n</ul>\n\n<p>This means day‑to‑day work has a clear public service purpose and real‑world impact.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"a-unique-partnership\">A unique partnership</h3>\n\n<p>The FFC is a working partnership between the <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/environment-agency\">Environment Agency</a> (EA) and the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.metoffice.gov.uk/\">Met Office</a>. It combines hydrology and meteorology in one national centre based at the <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://www.metoffice.gov.uk/about-us/contact/how-to-find-our-offices\">Met Office headquarters in Exeter</a>.</p>\n\n<p>Working as a joint team encourages collaboration across disciplines and organisations. This gives staff the opportunity to learn from different approaches and contribute to shared national objectives.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"world-class-expertise\">World class expertise</h3>\n\n<p>Our team is made up of a range of roles and professional backgrounds - with hydrology and meteorology at its core. Knowledge from other related disciplines such as oceanography and environmental science is also represented across the team. This allows for constant learning and development within everyday work.</p>\n\n<h3 id=\"team-culture\">Team culture</h3>\n\n<p>We are a close‑knit team of around 40 skilled staff, with a strong focus on collaboration and inclusion. We value teamwork and development - creating an environment where people feel supported and able to make meaningful contributions.</p>\n\n<p>This aligns with <a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/environment-agency/about/recruitment#value-difference-include-everyone\">Environment Agency</a> and <a rel=\"external\" href=\"https://careers.metoffice.gov.uk/supporting-you\">Met Office</a> commitments to inclusive working practices and flexible working.</p>\n\n<h2 id=\"contact-details-and-more-information\">Contact details and more information</h2>\n\n<p>You can read more about the FFC on our \n<a href=\"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/flood-forecasting-centre/about\">about us</a> \npage.</p>\n\n<p>To get in touch with us for any further information or enquiries, please email <a href=\"mailto:FFCenquiries@environment-agency.gov.uk\">FFCenquiries@environment-agency.gov.uk</a>.</p>\n</div>","change_history":[{"note":"The page has been updated to include new background information on working for the FFC.","public_timestamp":"2026-04-16T15:30:33Z"},{"note":"First published.","public_timestamp":"2021-07-21T14:14:30Z"}],"headers":[{"id":"current-vacancies","level":2,"text":"Current vacancies"},{"headers":[{"id":"meaningful-work","level":3,"text":"Meaningful work"},{"id":"a-unique-partnership","level":3,"text":"A unique partnership"},{"id":"world-class-expertise","level":3,"text":"World class expertise"},{"id":"team-culture","level":3,"text":"Team culture"}],"id":"our-team-and-how-we-work","level":2,"text":"Our team and how we work"},{"id":"contact-details-and-more-information","level":2,"text":"Contact details and more information"}],"organisation":"c99f2cd3-22e1-4bcf-83e5-d710d66501a3","tags":{"browse_pages":[]}},"document_type":"recruitment","first_published_at":"2021-07-21T15:14:30+01:00","links":{"available_translations":[{"api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/flood-forecasting-centre/about/recruitment","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/flood-forecasting-centre/about/recruitment","base_path":"/government/organisations/flood-forecasting-centre/about/recruitment","content_id":"2ac17710-6c01-4d45-a4bd-346ca52dff7c","document_type":"recruitment","links":{},"locale":"en","public_updated_at":"2026-04-16T15:30:33Z","schema_name":"corporate_information_page","title":"Working for FFC","web_url":"https://www.gov.uk/government/organisations/flood-forecasting-centre/about/recruitment","withdrawn":false}],"organisations":[{"analytics_identifier":"PB1335","api_path":"/api/content/government/organisations/flood-forecasting-centre","api_url":"https://www.gov.uk/api/content/government/organisations/flood-forecasting-centre","base_path":"/government/organisations/flood-forecasting-centre","content_id":"c99f2cd3-22e1-4bcf-83e5-d710d66501a3","details":{"acronym":"FFC","brand":"department-for-business-innovation-skills","default_news_image":{"high_resolution_url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/60f73579e90e0764d1be27fc/s960_Temporary_flood_defence_Thames_in_Oxford-rt-RGB_2.jpg","url":"https://assets.publishing.service.gov.uk/media/60f73579e90e0764cfc22a7b/s300_Temporary_flood_defence_Thames_in_Oxford-rt-RGB_2.jpg"},"logo":{"crest":"custo